<paragraph id="776C3686AD5CFFC0FF53FA438C37FA31" blockId="2.[136,1452,1172,1519]" box="[136,1380,1497,1519]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5CFFC0FF53FA438856FA31" bold="true" box="[136,261,1497,1519]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">Illustrations</emphasis>
:— 
<bibRefCitation id="13424B77AD5CFFC0FEFAFA438893FA30" author="Dahlstedt, H." box="[289,448,1497,1519]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" pagination="1" refId="ref3398" refString="Dahlstedt, H. (1907) Ueber einige im Bergianschen botanischen Garten in Stockholm kultivierte Taraxaca. Acta Horti Bergiani 4: [1] - 31, plate I, II." type="journal article" year="1907">Dahlstedt (1907</bibRefCitation>
, Plate II, fig. 40–43); herbarium images on JSTOR Global Plants pages (https://plants.jstor.org/).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="776C3686AD5CFFC1FF53F9878AB2FE97" blockId="2.[136,1452,1565,2060]" lastBlockId="3.[136,1452,158,509]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="298" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">
Description:—Plants usually medium-sized, often subrobust, most often up to 
<quantity id="B02B9B63AD5CFFC0FBDDF9878D1FF9E6" box="[1030,1100,1565,1592]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" unit="cm" value="17.0">17 cm</quantity>
tall. Leaves deep to dark midgreen, glabrous, rarely (in inner leaves proximally) with a few hairs on mid-vein‘s adaxial surface, usually 8–15 × 
<quantity id="B02B9B63AD5CFFC0FF53F9FF89A6F95E" box="[136,245,1637,1664]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.25" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" unit="cm" value="4.25" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.5">3.5–5 cm</quantity>
, young leaves often undivided or with 2–3 subrecurved lateral lobes and ± entire margins, middle leaves usually with 3–5 pairs of acute, narrowly triangular to ± triangular, subrecurved to subpatent lateral segments, distal margin most often sigmoid, usually with a single sub-basal tooth, or with a few little teeth, proximal margin concave, usually entire, often raised; terminal segment triangular or elongated-triangular, entire or with a single shallow incision, basal lobules narrow, acute; petiole glabrous, dark purple, narrow, unwinged; interlobes narrow, or up to 
<quantity id="B02B9B63AD5CFFC0FAFEF96C8C34F8CE" box="[1317,1383,1782,1808]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 mm</quantity>
wide, entire or with 1–2 thin teeth, margin often raised; mid-vein usually purplish. Scapes glabrous, usually purplish, ± equalling or slightly overtopping leaves. Capitulum deep yellow, (2.5–) 
<quantity id="B02B9B63AD5CFFC0FC17F8A78D6BF886" box="[972,1080,1853,1880]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.25" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" unit="cm" value="3.25" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="3.0">3–3.5 cm</quantity>
wide. Involucre dark (blackish) olivaceous-green, rounded and 
<quantity id="B02B9B63AD5CFFC0FE35F8FB8B1EF8A2" box="[494,589,1889,1916]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" unit="mm" value="8.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="8.0">8–9 mm</quantity>
wide at base. Outer phyllaries (12) 13–15 (16), appressed, subimbricate or not so, lanceolate, narrowly lanceolate, sometimes ovate-lanceolate, usually 6–8 (–9) × 
<quantity id="B02B9B63AD5CFFC0FB5FF81F8DA8F87E" box="[1156,1275,1925,1952]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" unit="mm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.0">2–2.5 mm</quantity>
, surface blackgreen, border sometimes not visible, sometimes paler, up to 
<quantity id="B02B9B63AD5CFFC0FCECF8338ADCF81A" box="[823,911,1961,1988]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
wide, margin ciliate, apex flat; inner phyllaries usually 12–13 mmlong, flat. Outer ligules flat to subcanaliculate, striped deep grey-green outside, often with purplish hue, ligule teeth blackish green. Pollen sometimes absent, usually present, pollen grains irregular in size. Stigmas discoloured, light greyish-greenish. Achenes castaneous-brown or medium dark mid-brown, 4.2–4.8 × 
<quantity id="B02B9B63AD5DFFC1FAC7FF048CF4FF67" box="[1308,1447,158,185]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.1">1.1–1.4 mm</quantity>
, body ± densely or subdensely covered with ± robust straight spinules and squamules up to 
<quantity id="B02B9B63AD5DFFC1FB78FF588C5AFF03" box="[1187,1289,194,221]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" unit="mm" value="0.35">0.35 mm</quantity>
long in upper 1/4–1/3, subabruptly to subgradually narrowing in a relatively robust subcylindrical cone ca. 0.6–0.9 × ca. 
<quantity id="B02B9B63AD5DFFC1FA8CFF7C89E5FEFB" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" unit="mm" value="0.45" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.4">0.4–0.5 mm</quantity>
, beak thin, 
<quantity id="B02B9B63AD5DFFC1FEE4FE9088CCFEFB" box="[319,415,266,293]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" unit="mm" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6–7 mm</quantity>
long, pappus ± yellowish white, ca. 
<quantity id="B02B9B63AD5DFFC1FC90FE908AF7FEFB" box="[843,932,266,293]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
long.—Agamosperm. 2n=32 (A. 
<bibRefCitation id="13424B77AD5DFFC1FAF2FE9089AFFE96" author="Krahulcova, A." pageId="3" pageNumber="298" pagination="289 - 294" refId="ref3866" refString="Krahulcova, A. (1993): New chromosome numbers in Taraxacum with reference to SAT-chromosomes. Folia Geobotanica Phytotaxonomica 28: 289 - 294. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 02853516" type="journal article" year="1993">Krahulcová 1993: 292</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="13424B77AD5DFFC1FED3FEB488A3FE96" author="Gustafsson, A." box="[264,496,302,328]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" pagination="41 - 62" refId="ref3519" refString="Gustafsson, A. (1932) Zytologische und experimentelle Studien in der Gattung Taraxacum. Hereditas 16: 41 - 62. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1601 - 5223.1932. tb 02561. x" type="journal article" year="1932">Gustafsson 1932: 48</bibRefCitation>
, both under the name of 
<taxonomicName id="B0D34D05AD5DFFC1FCDCFEB58A82FE96" box="[775,977,302,328]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schroeterianum">
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5DFFC1FCDCFEB58A82FE96" box="[775,977,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">T. schroeterianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="776C3686AD5DFFC1FF66FEC98AE9FE23" blockId="3.[136,1452,158,509]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">
<taxonomicName id="B0D34D05AD5DFFC1FF66FEC9888EFEB2" authorityName="Dahlstedt" authorityYear="1907" box="[189,477,338,364]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhodocarpum">
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5DFFC1FF66FEC9888EFEB2" box="[189,477,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">Taraxacum rhodocarpum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, known to occur in the 
<location id="720C605DAD5DFFC1FD21FEC98AC0FEB2" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:FF7A8790AD5CFFC1FF53FB0F8AE9FE23:720C605DAD5DFFC1FD21FEC98AC0FEB2" box="[762,915,338,365]" country="France" municipality="They" name="Western Alps" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">Western Alps</location>
of 
<collectingCountry id="0FC47616AD5DFFC1FC1BFEC98D5FFEB3" box="[960,1036,339,365]" name="France" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">France</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="0FC47616AD5DFFC1FB92FEC88D81FEB2" box="[1097,1234,338,364]" name="Switzerland" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
, is markedly close morphologically to the group of taxa around 
<taxonomicName id="B0D34D05AD5DFFC1FD41FEED8D6EFE4E" authority="van Soest (1959: 132)" authorityName="van Soest" authorityPageNumber="132" authorityYear="1959" box="[666,1085,374,401]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reophilum">
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5DFFC1FD41FEED8A7FFE4E" box="[666,812,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">T. reophilum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="13424B77AD5DFFC1FCECFEED8D6EFE4E" author="van Soest, J. L." box="[823,1085,374,401]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" pagination="77 - 138" refId="ref4344" refString="van Soest, J. L. (1959) Alpine species of Taraxacum. Acta Botanica Neerlandica 8: 77 - 138. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1438 - 8677.1959. tb 00013. x" type="journal article" year="1959">van Soest (1959: 132)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<collectingMunicipality id="9708ACFCAD5DFFC1FB91FEEC8DD7FE4E" box="[1098,1156,374,400]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">They</collectingMunicipality>
are very similar in outer phyllary characters and the robust achenes with a thick subcylindrical cone. 
<taxonomicName id="B0D34D05AD5DFFC1FC2DFE018DBDFE6A" box="[1014,1262,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reophilum">
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5DFFC1FC2DFE018DBDFE6A" box="[1014,1262,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">Taraxacum reophilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, is the 
<typeStatus id="A8688824AD5DFFC1FF53FE2589EBFE07" box="[136,184,447,473]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">type</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5DFFC1FF06FE2589A1FE06" box="[221,242,447,472]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">T.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5DFFC1FEE9FE2488CAFE06" box="[306,409,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">Alpestria</emphasis>
, and these two species therefore belong to the same section. The inevitable conclusion is that the name 
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5DFFC1FF2EFE798859FE22" box="[245,266,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">T.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5DFFC1FE91FE7888E2FE22" box="[330,433,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">Alpestria</emphasis>
is a younger synonym of 
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5DFFC1FD08FE798BBAFE22" box="[723,745,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">T.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5DFFC1FCF3FE788AE1FE22" box="[808,946,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">Rhodocarpa</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
